Date: 1995-12-18

Title: Low-Energy Scattering of Black Holes and p-branes in String Theory

Authors: R.R. Khuri and R.C. Myers

Comments: plain TeX, needs harvmac, 6 pages; Talk by RRK to appear in

Proceedings of Sixth Canadian Conference on General Relativity andRelativistic Astrophysics; for details see hep-th/9512061Journal-ref: Fields Inst. Comm. 15 (1997) 273

We discuss the low-energy dynamics of generalized extremal higher membraneblack hole solutions of string theory and higher membrane theories followingManton's prescription for multi-soliton solutions. A flat metric is found forthose solutions which possess $\kappa$-symmetry on the worldvolume.